<br/>
To @kalaskimchi , thank you for bringing your flavour into our kitchen. Korean kimchi and Cantonese dim sum on one table, it felt right.<br/>
<br/>
To our team and everyone behind the scenes, thank you for the long hours and steady hands.<br/>
<br/>
And to every guest who showed up, tasted, and trusted us, we’re grateful.<br/>
<br/>
This was more than a pop-up. It was a Copenhagen food collaboration we won’t forget.<br/>
<br/>
